nodes.label: message
nodes.text: Hi Person1, Patients on PI3 kinase inhibitors like Person2 can get a type of pneumonia called PCP pneumonia. Bactrim is an antibiotic given to prevent this. It is taken as one tablet on MM/DD/YYYY, MM/DD/YYYY, and MM/DD/YYYY. Please pick it up and start it. Let me know if you have any issues with it like rashes or diarrhea . Most people tolerate it fine 3 times per week. I realized you were not on it when I finalized my last note, and I thought I messaged you, but it sounds like I didn't. I apologize for the confusion.
